The information we collect is used exclusively for the following purposes:
- To deliver our intelligence insights and strategic alerts.
- To respond to professional inquiries or consulting requests.
- To improve the user experience and content relevance of **AutoChina.org**.

### 3. Data Security and Third-Party Sharing
We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data. **We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to outside parties.** Your data is processed only by authorized service providers for the purpose of maintaining our communication infrastructure and delivering requested content.

### 4. Cookies and Tracking
Our website may use essential cookies to enhance site navigation and analyze traffic patterns. This data is aggregated and anonymized, containing no personally identifiable information.

### 5. Your Rights and Opt-Out
You retain full control over your data. At any time, you may:
- Request access to the personal data we hold.
- Request the correction or deletion of your information.
- **Unsubscribe** from our communications via the opt-out link provided in our electronic correspondence.

### 6. Changes to This Policy
We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal obligations. Any updates will be posted on this page with an updated revision date.

### 7. Contact Us
For any questions regarding this policy, please contact our data compliance team at: **contact@autochina.org**.
